<p><b>The Wonder Boys <br>
  news</b></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><b>Nov 26, 2010:</b><br>
  We're terribly sorry for the lack of updates this recent year. It has to do 
  with extensive film work, a computer change, parental leave, and, well, more 
  film work, etc. The page has moved, and so did the mp3 server (hopefully those 
  links work again now). <br>
  Anyway, what's new since last time? <br>
  <br>
  Summer 2009 saw two special &quot;private&quot; live performances: <br>
  On Lars' and Nicole's wedding, Aug 1, 2009, the Honky Tonk Boys (Bj&ouml;rn 
  Radon on vocals, David on acoustic guitar and some backing vocals, and guest 
  start Tassilo Radon filling in for Lars, on a wonderful toy trumpet solo) performed 
  the DL-penned song &quot;Happy Blues&quot;. Please note Folklore Center legend 
  Izzy Young (Bob Dylan's old pal) in the left picture, sitting to the right!</p>
<p><img src="HTB_Izzy.jpg" width="677" height="283"></p>
<p>Two days later, David (sax) and his brother Dan (trumpet), played for their 
  dearly beloved Grandma, who turned 90 that day (her last birthday, as it sadly 
  turned out earlier this year). The set (once again) included &quot;Ja m&aring; 
  hon leva&quot; and &quot;V&auml;rmlandsvisan&quot;, and as an encore (which 
  may be of interest to the longtime TWB fan), a surprise impromptu performance 
  of... &quot;Sax Play&quot;! </p>
<p><img src="DoD_Mormor90.jpg" width="283" height="378"> 
</p>
<p>&quot;Den Flygande V&auml;rml&auml;nningen&quot; 7'' was for sale at <a href="http://207.228.243.82/ss/cat.html">S.S. 
  Records</a> for a while, but when I checked back now, it seems to be sold out 
  (at their place, that is - it's still available through Lystring, though). <br>
  &quot; I Detta Satans Rum&quot; was apparently played Dec 15 2009 at <a href="http://artforspastics.blogspot.com/">Art 
  for Spastics</a>. <br>
  <br>
  David's 58 min documentary &quot;Jakten p&aring; Bernhard&quot; (&quot;Traces 
  of Bernhard&quot;, Silverosa Film 2010, produced by Anna Byvald &amp; Lukas 
  Moodysson), was premiered at Gothenburg International Film Festival Jan 29, 
  2010. TWB fans should note that it also features Christian Kast&eacute;n behind 
  (and occasionally in front of) the camera; that the song &quot;Eva's Chair&quot; 
  (from &quot;The Grand Tradition Of Sitting Between Chairs&quot;) is included 
  in the soundtrack (mainly written and performed by David, with some excellent 
  help from old pal Mattias B&auml;rjed of Ants of the Underground, Nymphet Noodlers, 
  The Soundtrack Of Our Lives and Free Fall fame) and also &quot;Madrigal&quot; 
  (which is the mp3-only released &quot;A Story (1978)&quot;) without vocals); 
  that Bernhard is the man behind the lettering used for the TWB logo first used 
  inside the cd tray of the &quot;T.A.S.C.A.M. Manifesto&quot; album (later on 
  the front covers of &quot;The Grand Tradition...&quot; and &quot;Passion &amp; 
  Compassion&quot;). <br>
  &quot;Jakten p&aring; Bernhard&quot; was later shown on &quot;Doc Lounge&quot; 
  events in Malm&ouml; (Feb 15, Inkonst), Lund (Feb 16, Mejeriet), Stockholm (Feb 
  23, Allm&auml;nna Galleriet) and Gothenburg (March 2, House of Win-Win). The 
  Stockholm screening also included - apart from the &quot;Efterlysning: Space&quot; 
  short movie from 2002 - a rare, improvised live performance of &quot;Ett stycke 
  f&ouml;r Bernhard&quot; (&quot;A piece for Bernhard&quot;), by David (sax), 
  Jonas Ellerstr&ouml;m (electric guitar), David Enemar (sax) and Nicole Vickers 
  (clarinet) - more members were supposed to attend, but couldn't do so, due to 
  the terrible weather situation. <br>
  <br>
  <img src="JPB_Doc_L_improv.jpg" width="378" height="274"><br>
  <br>
  Swedish Television (SVT) showed &quot;Jakten p&aring; Bernhard&quot; on April 
  11, also had several re-runs the following week, and it was up for internet 
  viewing on SVT Play a whole month, until May 11. You can still catch a few minutes 
  <a href="http://svtplay.se/v/1948400/dokumentarfilm/klipp__jakten_pa_bernhard">here</a> 
  (until March 31, 2011), aswell as a <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1rWN7x1cP3M">trailer</a> 
  on Youtube. It was also shown at V&auml;rmlands Filmfestival, Arvika (April 
  17) and on the &quot;Pandoras ask&quot; exhibition at Galleri Verkligheten, 
  Ume&aring; (April 23 - May 7). There's also a fan page on Facebook. <br>
  (By the way, &quot;Horst - munspelskungen&quot; was shown July 10-11 in a pig 
  sty (!) at the &quot;Party Paradise no. 2&quot; event in &Aring;bytorp.)<br>
  <br>
  <img src="JPB-dvd.jpg" width="283" height="425"><br>
  <br>
  In mid-January 2011 (Jan 12, preliminary), Folkets Bio will release the dvd 
  &quot;Jakten p&aring; Bernhard och andra filmer av David Liljemark&quot;, which 
  includes the following material: <br>
  <br>
  * Jakten p&aring; Bernhard (58:00) <em>[which also has english subtitles]</em><br>
  * Post Scriptum till Jakten p&aring; Bernhard (12:08) <br>
  * Horst - munspelskungen (30:00) <em>[see Nov 15 &amp; Dec 18, 2006 entries 
  below]</em><br>
  * Efterlysning: Space (6:02) <br>
  * Fr&ouml;dings hj&auml;rna (0:47) <br>
  * Ett litet barn (24:06) <em>[see March 16, 2005 and May 26, 2009 entries below] 
  </em><br>
  * The Wonder Boys: My Old Friends (4:18) <br>
  * ...and a 5-track TWB audio loop (New Start [DL], The Night When The Losers 
  Won [CG/DL], Alstr&ouml;mer Disco [DL/CG], Sax Play [DL], A Gift I Never Had 
  [CG/DL]). <br>
  <br>
  Pretty neat, huh? Do NOT miss out! It's already advertised for pre-sale at <a href="http://www.discshop.se/filmer/dvd/jakten_pa_bernhard_och_andra_filmer_av_david_liljemark/P88010">Discshop</a> 
  and <a href="http://www.webhallen.com/film/dvd/115335-jakten_pa_bernhard">Webhallen</a>. 
</p>
