<b> Nov 15, 2006:<br>
</b>In case you've wondered what (previously) unsung hero who was the inspiration 
for the weird harmonica solo in &quot;Satan's Death Waltz&quot;, you'll know it 
for sure after seeing David's 30 min short documentary movie <a href="http://www.popcorn.nu/content/filmer/horst.html">&quot;Horst 
- munspelskungen&quot;</a> (&quot;Horst - the harmonica king&quot;), which will 
be shown (together with Josh Rubin's &quot;Derailroaded&quot; about Wild Man Fischer) 
at the <a href="http://www.popcorn.nu">Popcorn</a> music film festival (8-10 dec) 
in Stockholm, on Sunday 10 dec at Debaser Medis, starting 15:45 in the afternoon. 
