<p><b> April 29, 2006:<br>
  </b> News about &quot;related&quot; stuff: <br>
  The new 3'' cdr record label <a href="http://www.mussigganger.tk">M&uuml;&szlig;igg&auml;nger</a> 
  has a brand new release out by <a href="http://www.valand.gu.se/newmedia/97-98/gunnar/pages/dayw/sdalb1.html" target="_blank">Sugar</a> 
  <a href="http://www.valand.gu.se/newmedia/97-98/gunnar/movies/sugard.html" target="_blank">Daddy</a>: 
  &quot;nine-2-five&quot; (live at Lunds Konsthall, 21 Oct 1995 (mid-day show 
  - in the evening, &quot;6-6-6&quot; was performed)). Limited edition of only 
  33 numbered copies, hurry up to get one of these beautiful &amp; rare collector's 
  items! <a href="http://www.valand.gu.se/newmedia/97-98/gunnar/teori/sdbio.html">Sugar 
  Daddy</a> is David's noise jazz band, which was formed in Dec 1994 and has played 
  live 17 times since then; a total of 32 different people have so far participated 
  in the ever-changing line-up. <br>
  <br>
  <img src="Sugar_Daddy_3inchCD_9-2-5.jpg" width="91" height="113"> <br>
  <br>
  The second printing of David &amp; Christian K's children's &quot;pixi&quot; 
  book &quot;Knisen &amp; Kn&aring;kan har t&aring;rtkalas&quot; (&quot;The Cnow 
  &amp; The Pignet have a cake party&quot;) is now out in the stores; see May 
  2003 entry below (and Nov 28, 2005 entry aswell).</p>
