<b><br>
December 8, 2005:<br>
</b> The Wonder Boys = The Video Boys! <br>
Just in time for the Christmas season (although this day rather brings John Lennon 
to mind more than Santa Claus), The Wonder Boys proudly present their first, 100% 
authorized video: &#8221;<a href="http://www.droidlocks.com/mof_sorensen3.mov">My 
Old Friends</a>&#8221;! (Quicktime, ca 40 MB)
<p><a href="http://www.droidlocks.com/mof_sorensen3.mov"><img src="MOFtroll.jpg" width="198" height="154"><img src="MOFdayw.jpg" width="198" height="154"></a><br>
  <br>
  The track was recorded in 1998 and appeared on The Wonder Boys&#8217; first 
  release, the &#8220;<a href="http://www.geocities.com/iwannadieonstage/twbaiawns.html">...And 
  It&#8217;s A Wonderful, New Start</a>&#8221; cassette album (1999). The video 
  was filmed by David (and his brother Dan) about a year ago, and edited into 
  proper shape earlier this week with kind help from our excellent cutting room 
  master, mr <a href="http://www.droidlocks.com">Sam &#8220;Scraping Sampan Off 
  The Wheel&#8221; Sohlberg</a>. Enjoy, both old and new friends &#8211; and enemies! 
</p>
